There are 487 models in the zip file, covering 8 font-types, the following section list all available characters in each font-type:

curlzMT:
A-Z,0-9,a-z,&<>*@\{}^:,$.=!-[]_%+?();/

frenchscript:
A-Z,0-9,&<>*@{}^:$=!-#%+?();[]

harrington:
A-Z,0-9,&<>*@{}^$.!#%?()[]

lucidacalligraphy:
A-Z,0-9,&<>{}:?();[]

oldenglish:
A-Z,0-9,a-z,&<>*@^$!#%?()

perpetua:
A-Z,0-9,&<>*@{}^.=!-#+%?():[]

pristina:
A-Z,0-9,a-z,&<>*{}^@$=!#-%?{}[]

scriptMT:
A-Z

Or see the screenshot(in the attachement) for more graphical detail

surface property of CurlzMT, FrenchScript and Old English are defined as wood, weighed 25 in mass.

surface property of Harrington and Pristina are defined as metal, weighed 50 in mass.

Surface Property of LucidaCalligraphy, Perpetua and ScriptMT are defined as concrete, weighted 50 in mass.


All MDLs are providede with 3 skins, skin 0 are all the same base texture, skin 1 and 2 alter depends on its surface, see screenshot for detail.

polycount of each single model is varied from 50-220

NOTICE: Some mdls are not tested ingame because it is impossible to test all 500 mdls(with 3 skins, it will be app 1.5k combinations, even more impossible). If you can spot any flaws, please PM, email or post here to report the issue (during modelling, partial surface of texture was streched as a result of mass production, hence in this case, streched texture is not a flaw.

Due to the limited resolution provided, screenshots in the attachment have been resized without maintaining its aspect ratio. 

All models are stated "$staticprop" in qc files for compiling, further prop type can be made if requested.
All models are provided with simple physics box,a very simple 6 sided rectangular box.

No animation involved
Part of the textures have specular maps or normal maps

Software used: PS CS3, Lightwave 9.5

Installation Instructions:
Straight forward, simply extract the rar/zip file into cstrike folder, so that the paths:
x:\Program Files\Steam\steamapps\USER\counter-strike source\cstrike\models\models_kit
x:\Program Files\Steam\steamapps\USER\counter-strike source\cstrike\materials\models\models_kit
are both containing the files and valid directories

Please respect the right that i made these models. You are allowed to change the texture image, but my name "Mr. Kit" MUST be credited, either tagged onto texture image, written into a readme file or written as the map's credit. You are also welcome to distribute these models, also feel free to use them on your custom map. You are suposed to give me, Mr. Kit, credit while publlishing your map. Please contact me when you release your map to public, so that i can see how good/bad the models react ingame.

To see more of my models pack, please click on my name "mrkit4423" and click submission.
